This paper focuses on the impact of network state collection and distribution on the performance of SDN applications, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of controllers and load-balancing applications, which are relevant to the sub-categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also touches on security concerns related to outdated network information, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the simulation of a mathematical model, which could be relevant to the sub-category of programming languages (cs.PL).
